{
  "texts": [
    "A gradient-based search method was used for architecture search.",
    "The optimization process determined the assignment of different network nodes for each task and how these selected nodes were shared with other tasks.",
    "A unique characteristic of their work was the adoption of parameter sharing at the operator (neuron) level via a joint optimization of shared policies and network weights.",
    "Their yielded multi-task model showed great capabilities in tackling diverse multiclass semantic segmentation problems.",
    "In addition, automated production of search parameter and search mechanisms for metaheuristic algorithms was exploited by Stu ¨tzle and Lo ´pez-Iba ´n ˜ez [22]."
  ]
